<article>
    <h1>Sail&#xAD;ing on land</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200927/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-27"><time>2020-09-27</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | TRAVEL</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Over at Pas­sion WaVe @ Ma­rina Bay, Han­dle­bar’s sis­ter restau­rant and bar Kontiki is equally laid-back, but is an­chored by a nau­ti­cal theme to re­flect its lo­ca­tion by the wa­ter.</p>
    <p>The in­te­rior is de­signed to re­sem­ble a wooden hull, with lit­tle port­holes. Wooden oars serve as bar foot rests. Surf­boards sus­pended above the bar serve as shelves.</p>
    <p>A globe turned into a lamp­shade, a replica of the Ti­tanic, a wall­mounted wooden boat and a vin­tage at­las replica add to the nau­ti­cal theme. Port­hole win­dows give a peek into the kitchen.</p>
    <p>Cus­tomers can lounge in direc­tor chairs with blue-and-white striped can­vas seats and backs.</p>
    <p>The out­door din­ing area of­fers spec­tac­u­lar views of Ma­rina Bay and you can see the Sin­ga­pore Flyer and Gar­dens by the Bay.</p>
    <p>Cus­tomer favourites in­clude the Prawn Cock­tail ($13++) and Penne Car­bonara ($17++), which comes with crispy ba­con bits and an egg yolk with a liq­uid cen­tre.</p>
    <p>For brunch on week­ends, try the Sal­mon Av­o­cado Toast ($16++).</p>
    <p>For mock­tails, go for the Pas­sion­wave ($8++), which is made with Blue Cu­ra­cao, ly­chee syrup, lime, Sprite and soda wa­ter and gar­nished with fresh mint. The drink is re­fresh­ing and not overly sweet.</p>

